# 8. Factorial Using Recursion

Formula:

```
n! = n × (n-1)!
```

Example:

```
5! = 5×4×3×2×1
```

Code:

```java
static int factorial(int n) {

    if(n == 0)
        return 1;

    return n * factorial(n - 1);
}
```

Execution:

```
factorial(5)
=
5 × factorial(4)

=
5 × 4 × factorial(3)

=
5 × 4 × 3 × factorial(2)

=
5 × 4 × 3 × 2 × factorial(1)

=
5 × 4 × 3 × 2 × 1

=
120
```

Output:

```
120
```

---

# 9. Sum of First N Numbers

Formula:

```
1 + 2 + 3 + ... + n
```

Code:

```java
static int sum(int n) {

    if(n == 0)
        return 0;

    return n + sum(n - 1);
}
```

Example:

```
sum(4)

=
4 + sum(3)

=
4 + 3 + sum(2)

=
4 + 3 + 2 + sum(1)

=
4 + 3 + 2 + 1

=
10
```

---

# 10. Fibonacci Using Recursion

Series:

```
0 1 1 2 3 5 8 13 ...
```

Formula:

```
fib(n)
=
fib(n-1) + fib(n-2)
```

Code:

```java
static int fib(int n) {

    if(n <= 1)
        return n;

    return fib(n - 1) + fib(n - 2);
}
```

Example:

```
fib(5)

=
fib(4) + fib(3)

=
5
```

Output:

```
5
```

